    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the duck has about 5 min cooking time left, boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>duck jelly</strong> to a measuring jug<strong> </strong>with your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and<strong> cornflour</strong></p><p>Mix until fully combined, then stir in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [195ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [275ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and set aside – this is your <strong>gravy mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698926015864-x200.jpg",
